Caribbean and South America. A 12 Aug 2017 report quotes USA health officials indicating that the Zika outbreaks in the Caribbean and South America are waning and that has helped slow the spread of the mosquito-borne virus to Florida [and other localities in the USA] this year (2017).
http://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/experts-herd-immunity-us-slows-zika-florida-49179180

