Cases in various countries not mentioned above or more recent case numbers.

Americas. 16 Aug 2017. (reported) case numbers have fallen dramatically from their peak in January-March 2016 and not recovered this year (2017). Increased herd immunity from previous Zika virus infections has been suggested as one reason for the decline.
http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/08/zika-has-all-disappeared-americas-why

