Mexico
- National. 25 Jul 2017. (reported) 450 cases of whom 185 are pregnant. State most affected: Nayarit and municipalities most affected there: Santiago Ixcuintla (86 cases), Tepic, San Blas (11), Tuxpan (9), and Rosamorada (7).
https://www.vallartadaily.com/living/health/nayarit-reports-cases-zika-state/

- Puebla state. 30 Jun 2017. (registered) 14 cases 4 of whom pregnant.
http://www.unionpuebla.mx/articulo/2017/06/30/salud/puebla-con-baja-incidencia-en-casos-de-dengue-zika-y-chikungunya [in Spanish]
[A report dated 17 Aug 2017 mentions 65 cases so far this year (2017) in Puebla, the 5th most affected state in Mexico with 9 percent of the national total cases (https://www.centronline.mx/contenido/2017/08/17/112535/Aviso.aspx in Spanish). - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

