South America
---
Argentina (Salta province). 13 Aug 2017. November 2016-May 2017, 1st locally acquired outbreak (conf.) 203 cases of which 7 pregnant. Department most affected: San Martín (Tartagal, General Mosconi, Aguaray, and Embarcación), and Morillo.
http://www.eltribuno.info/salta/nota/2017-8-13-0-0-0-hubo-203-casos-de-zika-en-el-primer-brote-autoctono [in Spanish]

Brazil
- Origin and spread. 15 Jun 2017. (reported) Analyses of viral genomes with ecological and epidemiological data yield an estimate that ZIKV was present in northeast Brazil by February 2014 and is likely to have disseminated from there, nationally and internationally, before the 1st detection of ZIKV in the Americas. Estimated dates for the international spread of ZIKV from Brazil indicate the duration of pre-detection cryptic transmission in recipient regions. The role of northeast Brazil in the establishment of ZIKV in the Americas is further supported by geographic analysis of ZIKV transmission.
http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v546/n7658/full/nature22402.html

- Eye lesions. 17 Jul 2017 (reported) of 112 infants born to Zika virus infected mothers in Brazil, 24 (21 percent) had eye abnormalities; 10 infants (42 percent) with abnormal eye examination findings did not have microcephaly, 8 (33 percent) did not have any central nervous system findings, and 2 (8 percent) had eye abnormalities despite maternal 3rd trimester infection. Eye abnormalities may be the only initial finding in congenital Zika virus infection, and all infants with potential Zika virus exposure should undergo screening eye examinations. http://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapediatrics/article-abstract/2636587

Peru
- National. 22 Jul 2017. 2016-22 Jul 2017 (susp.) 6432 cases, (conf.) 1438 cases with 264 pregnant with 17 cases of suspected Zika virus-related microcephaly. For 2017 up to 23 Jul 2017 (susp.) 5552 cases, (conf.) 649 cases with 172 pregnant, 5 cases of suspected Zika virus-related microcephaly. Epidemic peak on week 15 [week ending 14 Apr 2017], then sharp decline.
http://www.dge.gob.pe/portal/docs/vigilancia/boletines/2017/29.pdf [in Spanish]

- Piura region. 29 Jul 2017. (susp.) 94 cases, (conf.) 13 cases of whom 5 pregnant.
http://diariocorreo.pe/edicion/piura/casos-de-dengue-y-zika-aumentan-ligeramente-semana-a-semana-764780/ [in Spanish]

