Viet Nam (Dak Lak province). August 2017. (reported) in June, 2016, a girl was born with microcephaly in Dak Lak Province, in the Central Highlands region of Viet Nam, at 37 weeks of gestation. The infant's mother (aged 23 years) had experienced symptoms of fever and rash associated with Zika virus infection during her 2nd trimester. The symptoms resolved uneventfully.
http://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(17)30412-7/fulltext

[Maps of Viet Nam can be seen at http://www.onlineasiatravel.com/images/vn/vietnam-map.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5261363,62774. - Mod.TY]

